    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Noam Elkies</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Noam_Elkies.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Noam_Elkies.jpg/330px-Noam_Elkies.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2b/Noam_Elkies.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Noam_Elkies.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noam_Elkies\">Noam Elkies</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Noam David Elkies</b>,<br />\nan American chess player, <a href=\"/Chess_Problems,_Compositions_and_Studies\" title=\"Chess Problems, Compositions and Studies\">composer of chess studies</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, mathematician and professor at Department of Mathematics, <a href=\"/Harvard_University\" title=\"Harvard University\">Harvard University</a>. His research interests covers <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatorial_game_theory\">combinatorial game theory</a>, and he is renowned for his knowledge of the connections between mathematics and music as well as chess and mathematics. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1996_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1996 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2005_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2005 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2015_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Noam_Elkies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1996_...\">1996 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Noam_Elkies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1996 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a> (<b>1996</b>). <i>On numbers and endgames: Combinatorial game theory in chess endgames</i>. in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://library.msri.org/books/Book29/index.html\">Games of No Chance</a> edited by <a href=\"/Richard_J._Nowakowski\" title=\"Richard J. Nowakowski\">Richard J. Nowakowski</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a> (<b>1999</b>). <i>On numbers and endgames: Combinatorial game theory in chess endgames</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/math/9905198\">arXiv:math/9905198</a>, differs only in trivial stylistic details from the (<b>1996</b>) version published in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://library.msri.org/books/Book29/index.html\">Games of No Chance</a> edited by <a href=\"/Richard_J._Nowakowski\" title=\"Richard J. Nowakowski\">Richard J. Nowakowski</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Noam_Elkies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a> (<b>2000</b>). <i>Higher Nimbers in pawn endgames on large chessboards</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0011253\">arXiv:math/0011253</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a> (<b>2001</b>). <i>Endgame Tables and Chess Composition</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#24_2\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICGA Journal, Vol. 24, No. 2</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a> (<b>2002</b>). <i>Higher Numbers in pawn endgames on large chessboards</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://library.msri.org/books/Book42/\">More Games of No Chance</a> edited by <a href=\"/Richard_J._Nowakowski\" title=\"Richard J. Nowakowski\">Richard J. Nowakowski</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#RPStanley\" title=\"Mathematician\">Richard P. Stanley</a> (<b>2003</b>). <i>The Mathematical Knight</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Mathematical_Intelligencer\">The Mathematical Intelligencer</a>, Vol. 25, No. 1, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.math.harvard.edu/%7Eelkies/knight.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a>, <a href=\"/Mark_Watkins\" title=\"Mark Watkins\">Mark Watkins</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Elliptic Curves of Large Rank and Small Conductor</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arxiv.org/abs/math/0403374\">arXiv:math/0403374</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.springer.com/mathematics/numbers/book/978-3-540-22156-2\">LNCS 3076</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2005_...\">2005 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Noam_Elkies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2005 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a> (<b>2005</b>). <i>New directions in enumerative chess problems</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electronic_Journal_of_Combinatorics\">Electronic Journal of Combinatorics</a>, Vol. 11, No. 2, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0508645\">arXiv:math/0508645</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/John_H._Conway\" title=\"John H. Conway\">John H. Conway</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.math.ku.edu/~jmartin/\">Jeremy L. Martin</a> (<b>2006</b>). <i>The Mathieu Group M 12 and Its Pseudogroup Extension M 13</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Experimental_Mathematics_%28journal%29\">Experimental Mathematics</a>, Vol. 15, No. 2 <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#RPStanley\" title=\"Mathematician\">Richard P. Stanley</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i>Chess and Mathematics</i>. excerpt, 6 Retrograde Analysis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www-math.mit.edu/%7Erstan/chess/spg.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/k/Kominers:Scott_Duke\">Scott D. Kominers</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i>On the Classification of Type II Codes of Length 24</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/0902.1942\">arXiv:0902.1942</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Dan_Heisman\" title=\"Dan Heisman\">Dan Heisman</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i>Steinitz, Zermelo, and Elkies</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ChessCafe.com\">ChessCafe.com</a>, on <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wilhelm_Steinitz\">Wilhelm Steinitz</a>, <a href=\"/Ernst_Zermelo\" title=\"Ernst Zermelo\">Ernst Zermelo</a> and <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Noam_Elkies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i>Every even number greater than 454 is the sum of seven cubes</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1009.3983\">arXiv:1009.3983</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/k/Kominers:Scott_Duke\">Scott D. Kominers</a> (<b>2011</b>). <i>Weighted Generating Functions for Type II Lattices and Codes</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1111.2392\">arXiv:1111.2392</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2015_...\">2015 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Noam_Elkies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2015 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/k/Kominers:Scott_Duke\">Scott D. Kominers</a> (<b>2015</b>). <i>Configurations of Extremal Type II Codes</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1503.04297\">arXiv:1503.0429</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Noam Elkies</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/s/Swaminathan:Ashvin_A=\">Ashvin Swaminathan</a> (<b>2016</b>). <i>Permutations that Destroy Arithmetic Progressions in Elementary p-Groups</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1601.07541\">arXiv:1601.07541</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Noam_Elkies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noam_Elkies\">Noam Elkies from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://genealogy.math.ndsu.nodak.edu/id.php?id=22514\">The Mathematics Genealogy Project - Noam Elkies</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://owpdb.mfo.de/person_detail?id=8109\">Details for Noam D. Elkies</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_Research_Institute_of_Oberwolfach\">Oberwolfach Photo Collection</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.math.harvard.edu/%7Eelkies/\">Noam D. Elkies Home Page</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.math.harvard.edu/%7Eelkies/chess.html\">Noam D. Elkies Chess Pages Links</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.math.harvard.edu/~elkies/math_cv.html\">Noam D. Elkies: Mathematics Curriculum Vitae</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.janko.at/Retros/Records/ShortestMate/Type2/index.htm\">Shortest Mates in Proof Games</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Noam_Elkies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Photo 2007 by Renate Schmid, MFO, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://owpdb.mfo.de/person_detail?id=8109\">Details for Noam D. Elkies</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_Research_Institute_of_Oberwolfach\">Oberwolfach Photo Collection</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?title=Category:Pictures_from_Oberwolfach_Photo_Collection&amp;filefrom=Kohnen+winfried.jpg#mw-category-media\">Category:Pictures from Oberwolfach Photo Collection - Wikimedia Commons</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessbase.com/newsdetail.asp?newsid=1919\">World Champion Dr GM GM John Nunn</a>, from <a href=\"/ChessBase\" title=\"ChessBase\">ChessBase News</a>, September 22, 2004</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.math.harvard.edu/%7Eelkies/chess.html\">Noam D. Elkies Chess Pages Links</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.informatik.uni-trier.de/~ley/pers/hd/e/Elkies:Noam_D=.html\">dblp: Noam D. Elkies</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">This article is based on a presentation given at the banquet in honor of  <a href=\"/Mathematician#RPStanley\" title=\"Mathematician\">Richard Stanley's</a> 60th birthday, and is dedicated to Stanley on this occasion</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathieu_group_M12\">Mathieu group M12 from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=